Goncalo Amaral ran the initial investigation into the disappearance of Madeleine McCann in 2007 . 
  He claimed in a book and a documentary that the McCanns were involved in her disappearance . 
  Lisbon court ordered him to pay £179,000 in damages and ban further sales of book . 
  He also told to pay interest on the £360,000 he was ordered to pay . 
 